# Read Rules & Skills Before Responding

Before answering any question or starting any task, you MUST:

1. Read `.cursor/rules/general.mdc` and say the magic words written in it to confirm you've read it
2. If a relevant skill is being triggered, read the full `SKILL.md` file before acting on it — skills contain required instructions

## Why

Rules contain project-specific conventions, constraints, and magic confirmation words. Skipping them causes incorrect assumptions, style violations, and missed context.

## Checklist (every session)

- [ ] Read `general.mdc` → say the magic words
- [ ] Read any triggered skill's `SKILL.md` before executing it
